content.description: Sit start on jugs, try not to slide down the rock slab. Make some throws to juggy slopers and top out. Definitely want a spotter in case you pop to keep you from tumbling down the rock. Super fun, albeit a bit dirty/sandy. With some cleaning and traffic, this climb would be a classic!
content.location: Directly to the right of Turtlehead

content.description: Start low under the prow compressing on a left-hand pocket/dish and a right hand lip.  Compress your way up the prow.  Dyno for a juggy ledge straight above you, and top out by moving right.
content.protection: A few pads and a spotter.  The landing isn't terrible, but there are some rocks around/under you as you climb--nothing jagged or too gnarly though.
content.location: Walk up the main trail past the Baby's Got Biceps boulder.  When the trail meets the creek bed, Turtlehead is the obvious prow on the left side of the creek bed.

content.description: Deadhang on two slopers about head height or try and smear your feet on the blank face below. Detached rock under the boulder is off. Campus up to a jug block, then commit to the funky topout. Probably wanna clean it up a little
content.protection: Pad or two. Spotter for confidence boost on the top
content.location: Upwash about 15 yards from Turtlehead and on the left.
